Change the atom to: 73-4.56. Change them to 3. To prove out that the collapse works: a. refactor collapsed methods, then rebuild and/or adjust database (parameterize, if necessary), and repeat Step 7 and 8 until the two old test cases fails and the new case passes per the requirement. The trick is make the test runner fail with a graceful popup at runtime or a Python KeyError: '73-4.xx' during mk_db.sh until correctly merged. 9. On the SP800-73-4 tab, locate the old atom rows, removed them, save, and rebuild the database. The next test should run with no unexpected failures and no popups.
